### File Naming Conventions
- **Classes**: PascalCase (e.g., `CharacterManager.gd`, `CampaignState.gd`)
- **Scene files**: PascalCase (e.g., `CharacterCreator.tscn`, `BattleMap.tscn`)
- **Resource files**: snake_case (e.g., `character_template.tres`, `weapon_data.res`)
- **Test files**: snake_case with `_test` suffix (e.g., `character_manager_test.gd`)
- **Interfaces**: Prefix with `I` (e.g., `ICharacter.gd`, `ICampaignPhase.gd`)
- **Enums**: Suffix with `Enums` (e.g., `FiveParsecsGameEnums.gd`, `CombatEnums.gd`)

### Class Naming Patterns
- **Base classes**: `Base{Type}` (e.g., `BaseMission`, `BaseCharacter`)
- **Interfaces**: `I{Type}` (e.g., `ICombatable`, `IStorable`)
- **Implementations**: `FiveParsecs{Type}` (e.g., `FiveParsecsMission`, `FiveParsecsCharacter`)
- **Managers**: `{Type}Manager` (e.g., `CombatManager`, `CampaignManager`)
- **UI Components**: `{Type}Component` (e.g., `InventoryComponent`, `CharacterSheet`)

